	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Nes 50/60hz workaround?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey everyone.<br /><br />As you all know or should know by now.<br />The pal nes can't be modified to output ntsc.<br />But i recently thought to myself:<br />what if i overclock the pal cpu to get a similar game-speed as the ntsc nes?<br />Of course it will still output pal but at least the speed will be the ntsc like speed for all the slowed down games like castlevania.<br /><br />Would this be possible?<br /><br />Greets

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Bregalad</b> [ Thu Jun 20, 2013 1:50 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Nes 50/60hz workaround?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It won't work. You could fix the music pitch by overclocking but that's it. The VBlank interrupts will still happen at 50 Hz.<br /><br />If you overclock both the PPU and the CPU then the VBlank interrupts could happen at 60 Hz, resulting in a normal game speed, but then the video signal would be completely wrong, and very probably unusable.<br /><br />In other words : It is cheaper/simpler to buy a famicom <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


