	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you overclock both the PPU and the CPU then the VBlank interrupts could happen at 60 Hz, resulting in a normal game speed, but then the video signal would be completely wrong, and very probably unusable.</div><br /><br />Would it though? PAL60 is often an unofficially supported quasi-standard. The only remaining issue I see is the line rate which at 625/60 would generate an 18.7KHz video signal which might be out of range for a TV set.

		

		</td>
